text: :For the village in Scotland, see Dunino. Dunino (; ) is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Krotoszyce, within Legnica County, Lower Silesian Voivodeship, in south-western Poland. It lies approximately south- west of Legnica, and west of the regional capital Wrocław. The village has a population of 120. ==References== Dunino
